  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ct to its perfection. Consequently, on the other hand, death, sickness, and all defects of the body are due to the lack of the body's subjection to the soul . It is therefore evident that as the rebellion of the carnal appetite against the spirit is a punishment of our first par</data>
