  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q164.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">against the reason: nor was the body wholly subject to the soul ; whence arose death and other bodily defects. For life and soundness of body depend on the body being subject to the soul , as the perfectible is subject to its perfection. Consequently, on the other</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">adams_first_sin</data>
