  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">As the Apostle says ( 1 Timothy 1:5 ), "the end of the commandment is charity ," which is enjoined upon us in the two precepts concerning the love of God and of our neighbor. Wherefore the decalogue contains those precepts which tend more directly to the love</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
  <data key="d19">precept</data>
  <data key="d20">precept | precept_linkage</data>
